---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const TELEGRAM = 'https://t.me/culoton';
const CONTRACT = 'EQD5dCm196cT60OTcCz_MI_f_QtpZYGU5mazX-4rjAOHiKrJ';
---

<Layout
  locale="en"
  pathWithoutLocale="/culo"
  title="$CULO — The native token of CuloTon"
  description="$CULO is a legacy meme token now live on TON. Multi-chain track record: 10,000X on Polygon, success on SUI, now bringing it home on TON."
>
  <article class="news-article">
    <div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 28px;">
      <img src="/culo.png" alt="$CULO token" style="width: 140px; height: 140px; border-radius: 50%; border: 3px solid var(--accent); margin: 0 auto;" />
    </div>

    <h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: var(--accent); font-family: var(--font-mono);">$CULO</span></h1>

    <p class="article-summary" style="text-align: center; border-left: none; padding-left: 0;">
      A legacy meme token — multi-chain veteran, now live on the TON blockchain.
    </p>

    <div class="ton-cta-row">
      <a class="cta-btn cta-primary" href={TELEGRAM} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Join Telegram →
      </a>
      <a class="cta-btn cta-secondary" href={`https://tonviewer.com/${CONTRACT}`} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        View on Tonviewer
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="contract-box">
      <span class="contract-label">Contract Address (TON)</span>
      <code class="contract-value" id="contract-value">{CONTRACT}</code>
      <button class="copy-btn" type="button" id="copy-btn" data-value={CONTRACT}>Copy</button>
    </div>

    <div class="body">
      <h2 style="font-size: 22px; margin-top: 36px; color: var(--accent);">Understanding $CULO on TON</h2>

      <p>
        Culo is a legacy meme spanning blockchains since early 2024. The team achieved a phenomenal
        <strong>10,000X move in MCAP on Polygon</strong>, attracting names like <em>CryptosRUS, JAKE, RODNEY,
        Crypto Crow, Wendy O</em> and <em>WARREN SAPP</em>, among many others.
      </p>

      <p>
        The project also achieved significant success on the <strong>SUI</strong> network, proving its
        resilience across different ecosystems. We are now committed to following that same path of massive
        growth on <strong>TON</strong> — including the launch of this dedicated website and a comprehensive
        development roadmap.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 22px; margin-top: 36px; color: var(--accent);">Track record</h2>
      <ul class="track-record">
        <li><strong>2024 — Polygon:</strong> 10,000X market-cap move; coverage and shoutouts from major crypto KOLs</li>
        <li><strong>SUI:</strong> Strong follow-through on a second chain — proven cross-ecosystem traction</li>
        <li><strong>2026 — TON:</strong> Launch on the network with native Telegram distribution and the CuloTon news platform</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size: 22px; margin-top: 36px; color: var(--accent);">Why TON</h2>
      <p>
        TON — The Open Network, originally conceived by Telegram — is one of the fastest-growing blockchains of
        2025-2026. With native Telegram integration, sub-second finality, and a rapidly expanding ecosystem of
        mini-apps and DeFi protocols, TON is uniquely positioned to bring crypto to hundreds of millions of
        Telegram users. $CULO arrives on TON with momentum from two prior chains and a community that already
        knows how to ship.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 22px; margin-top: 36px; color: var(--accent);">Community</h2>
      <p>
        The fastest way to get involved is the official Telegram group:
        <a href={TELEGRAM} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">{TELEGRAM}</a>.
        News, announcements and trade chatter all happen there.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 22px; margin-top: 36px; color: var(--accent);">Disclaimer</h2>
      <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-mute);">
        Nothing on this page is financial advice. $CULO is a memecoin; cryptocurrencies are highly volatile
        and you may lose your entire investment. Past performance on Polygon or SUI is no guarantee of future
        results on TON or any other chain. Always do your own research and only buy what you can afford to
        lose. CuloTon news coverage is editorially independent of token activity.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .ton-cta-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin: 24px 0 12px;
  }
  .cta-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 12px 22px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 14px;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    transition: transform 0.12s, opacity 0.12s;
  }
  .cta-btn:hover { transform: translateY(-1px); opacity: 0.92; }
  .cta-primary { background: var(--accent); color: #1a1408 !important; }
  .cta-secondary {
    background: transparent;
    border: 1px solid var(--ton);
    color: var(--ton) !important;
  }

  .contract-box {
    margin: 18px auto 0;
    background: var(--bg-elev);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  .contract-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--text-mute);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .contract-value {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 200px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text);
    word-break: break-all;
    background: transparent;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .copy-btn {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #1a1408;
    border: none;
    padding: 6px 14px;
    border-radius: 5px;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    cursor: pointer;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
  .copy-btn:hover { opacity: 0.9; }
  .copy-btn.copied { background: #4ade80; }

  .track-record {
    padding-left: 20px;
    margin: 16px 0;
  }
  .track-record li {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }
  .track-record strong {
    color: var(--text);
  }
</style>

<script is:inline>
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const btn = document.getElementById('copy-btn');
    if (!btn) return;
    btn.addEventListener('click', async () => {
      const value = btn.getAttribute('data-value') || '';
      try {
        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(value);
        const original = btn.textContent;
        btn.textContent = 'Copied!';
        btn.classList.add('copied');
        setTimeout(() => {
          btn.textContent = original;
          btn.classList.remove('copied');
        }, 1500);
      } catch (e) {
        btn.textContent = 'Copy failed';
      }
    });
  });
</script>
